sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1443000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part is a protein expression test unit with blue light receptor. It consists of a medium strength Anderson promoter (BBa_J23106), YF1 and FixJ light receptor system coupled with strong RBSs (BBa_K592016), a double terminator (BBa_B0015), the FixK2 promoter (BBa_K592006) and a strong RBS (BBa_B0034).
You have to add the gene of your interest coupled with a terminator for the device to work. With this part you can test and modify the protein expression intensity with blue light.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Minnamari Salmela

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: B0034-YF1-B0034-FixJ, blue light sensor and RR with RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: YF1 works in conjunction with its response regulator, FixJ. This part consists of RBS-coupled YF1 and FixJ without promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The components that made up of YF1 fusion protein comes from Bradyrhizobium japonicum and Bacillus subtilis. FixJ comes from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This constructs Strong RBS to ensure good expression.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K823008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Anderson promoter J23106 without RFP in backbone vector pSB1C3 to easily fuse the promoter with other reporters e.g. the lux operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Korinna Kraft

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: YF1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: YF1 is a fusion protein of YtvA (B.subtilis) and FixL(Br.japonicum). It contains the N-terminal region of YtvA (1-127) and C-terminal region of FixL (258-505), interconnected by a helical linker. This fusion protein is designed by Andreas Moglich and Keith Moffat. As shown in previous research, Illumination of the fusion kinase YF1 reduced net kinase activity by ∼1000-fold in vitro. YF1 also controls gene expression in a light-dependent manner in vivo.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Ytva comes from the genome of Bacillus subtilis.
FixL derives from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence information was provided in Moglich and Moffat's article. The physical DNA was synthesized by GenScript. Codon-optimization may enhance its expression.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: FixK2 promoter is the wild-type promoter to which phospho-FixJ binds. FixJ in turn can be regulated by YF1, the blue light-sensing protein. This promoter shows very little leaky activity in the absence of FixJ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: FixK2 promoter omes from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence information was provided by Moffat (Moffat et al. 2009). The DNA was synthesized by GenScript.
